    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I open neovim with extui enabled, I press :h to open help while being in oil.nvim buffer, I have autocommand setup to open oil.nvim preview and I have autocomplete in cmdline, when I press any cmdline command neovim crashes on this assertion.\n\nYes its fairly specific but if I disable any of:\n\noil.nvim autocmd that throws error,\nnvim extui,\ncmdline autocomplete using autocmd\n\nit stops so I think it might be related to multiline error message popping up while opening cmdline with multiple windows open maybe?\n\nScreenshots:\n\nAfter `:h`:\n\n<img width=\"2364\" height=\"1485\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7ea26b7c-3e3d-42c4-b856-3cda7c1bafba\" />\n\nAfter starting to write `:q`:\n\n<img width=\"1572\" height=\"965\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/68cf562d-53ed-440a-be64-9da6594df809\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI can consistently reproduce it with my dotfiles: https://github.com/deathbeam/dotfiles/tree/master/nvim/.config/nvim\n\nBut other than what I said above I wasnt able to narrow it down more.\n\nHere is extui enable: https://github.com/deathbeam/dotfiles/blob/af693d7db80794522be4dfda93e2b4b8cc3f90be/nvim/.config/nvim/lua/config/ui.lua#L13\n\nHere is oil autocmd:\nhttps://github.com/deathbeam/dotfiles/blob/af693d7db80794522be4dfda93e2b4b8cc3f90be/nvim/.config/nvim/lua/config/ui.lua#L86\n\nAnd here is the cmdline autocomplete:\nhttps://github.com/deathbeam/myplugins.nvim/blob/dc0af1afddf6a0801dc6940b7d2ee4a338bdd677/lua/myplugins/cmdcomplete.lua#L14\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo crash (or no fail on assert at least, I assume the assert is there for a reason and this should not happen)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1099+gbcf952e85f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno extui there so cant reproduce\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux archlinux 6.16.1-arch1-1.1-g14 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Fri, 22 Aug 2025 06:17:23 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.15.1 (0c405d53)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsource (RelWithDebInfo)",
